#: includes/class-settings-page.php:485
msgid "Most blocks store their content in one place — either as block attributes (the JSON between the wp:block comments) or as innerHTML. A few blocks store the same data in BOTH at the same time. For these, updating one without the other corrupts the block silently."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-settings-page.php:490
msgid "A common example is <code>yoast/faq-block</code>: it keeps the questions in <code>attributes.questions</code> AND in the inner <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> markup. If an agent updates only innerHTML, the structured questions array goes stale."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-settings-page.php:496
msgid "Block MCP detects most dual-storage blocks automatically by scanning your site. List any extras here (one per line) — when an agent tries to update one of these blocks, it will be required to send both attributes and innerHTML together, preventing the corruption."
msgstr ""

